et]]\"\n|-\n|2014\n|''The Money''\n|Ellen Knox\n|Television Movie\n|}\n\n=== Theatre ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n! Venue \n|-\n|1952\n|''The Climate of Eden''\n|Mabel\n|[[Martin Beck Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1953-54 \n|''The Seven Year Itch''\n|The Girl\n|[[Aldwych Theatre]], London \n|-\n|1954\n|''[[The Crucible]]''\n|Elizabeth Proctor\n|[[Bristol Old Vic]], London \n|-\n|1956\n|''[[Troilus and Cressida]]''\n|Cressida\n|[[Winter Garden Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1957\n|''The Glass Eye''\n|Dorothy Witley\n|[[American National Theater and Academy|ANTA Playhouse]], New York\n|-\n|1958\n|''Interlock''\n|Hilde\n|[[ANTA Playhouse]], New York \n|-\n|1958\n|''The Disenchanted''\n|Jere Halliday\n|[[Eugene O'Neill Theatre|Coronet Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1960\n|''The Tumbler''\n|Lennie\n|[[Helen Hayes Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1963\n|''[[Uncle Vanya]]''\n|Ilyena \n|[[Chichester Festival Theatre]], London\n|-\n|1963\n|''[[Hamlet (play)|Hamlet]]''\n| Ophelia\n| [[Old Vic Theatre]], London \n|-\n|1965\n|''Judith''\n|Judith\n| rowspan=3|[[Phoenix Theatre (New York City)|Phoenix Theatre]], Off-Broadway\n|-\n|1965\n|''[[Man and Superman]]''\n|Violet Robinson\n|-\n|1965\n|''War and Peace''\n|[[Natasha Rostova]]\n|-\n|1965 \n|''Herakles'' \n|Megara\n|[[Lyceum Theatre (Broadway)|Lyceum Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1966\n|''[[The Lion in Winter]]''\n|Eleanor\n|[[Ambassador Theatre (New York City)|Ambassador Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1966\u201367\n|''[[The School for Scandal]]''\n|Lady Teazle\n|rowspan=6|[[Lyceum Theatre (Broadway)|Lyceum Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1966\n|''[[Right You Are (if you think so)|Right You Are If You Think You Are]]''\n|Signora Ponza\n|-\n|1966\n|''We, Comrades Three''\n|Young Woman\n|-\n|1967\n|''[[The Wild Duck]]''\n|Gina\n|-\n|1967\n|''[[You Can't Take It with You (play)|You Can't Take it With You]]''\n|Alice Sycamore\n|-\n|1967\n|''War and Peace''\n|[[Natasha Rostova]]\n|-\n|1971\u201372\n|''[[Old Times]]''\n|Anna\n|[[Nederlander Theatre|Billy Rose Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1973\n|''[[The Merchant of Venice]]''\n|Portia\n|rowspan=2|[[Vivian Beaumont Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1973\n|''[[A Streetcar Named Desire|A Street Car Named Desire]]''\n|[[Blanche DuBois|Blanche Du Bois]]\n|-\n|1975\u201376\n|''[[The Royal Family (play)|The Royal Family]]''\n|Julie Cavendish\n|[[Brooklyn Academy of Music]] <br/> [[Helen Hayes Theatre]], Broadway \n|-\n|1977 || ''The New York Idea'' || Vida Phillimore || rowspan=2|[[Brooklyn Academy of Music]] \n|-\n|1977 || ''[[Three Sisters (play)|The Three Sisters]]'' || Olga\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1983\n|rowspan=2|''[[Heartbreak House]]''\n|rowspan=2|Hesione Hushabye\n|[[Circle in the Square Theatre]], Off-Broadway\n|-\n|[[Royal Shakespeare Company|Theatre Royal]], London \n|-\n|1985\n|''[[Pack of Lies]]''\n|Barbara Jackson\n|[[Bernard B. Jacobs Theatre|Royale Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1985\u201386\n|''[[Hay Fever (play)|Hay Fever]]''\n|Judith Bliss\n|[[Music Box Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1991\u201393\n|''[[Lost in Yonkers]]''\n|Grandma Kurnitz\n|[[Richard Rogers Theatre]], Broadway <br/> [[Royal Strand Theatre]], London\n|-\n|1994\u201395\n|''[[An Inspector Calls]]''\n|Sybil Birling\n|[[Bernard B. Jacobs Theatre|Royale Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1996\n|''[[A Delicate Balance (play)|A Delicate Balance]]''\n|Agnes\n|[[Plymouth Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|1999\n|''[[Waiting in the Wings (play)|Waiting in the Wings]]''\n|May Davenport\n|[[Walter Kerr Theatre]], Broadway <br/> [[Eugene O'Neill Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[All Over]]''\n|The Wife\n|[[Gramercy Theatre]], New York City\n|-\n|2005 \n|''The Other Side''\n|Levana Julak\n|[[Manhattan Theatre Club]], Off-Broadway\n|-\n|2007\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Oscar and the Lady in Pink (novel)|Oscar and the Lady in Pink]]''\n| rowspan= 2|Performer \n|[[Old Globe Theatre]], San Diego \n|-\n|2008\n|Florence Gould Hall, New York City \n|-\n|2009\n|''[[The Royal Family (play)|The Royal Family]]''\n|Fanny Cavendish\n|[[Samuel J. Friedman Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[The Road to Mecca (play)|The Road to Mecca]]''\n|Miss Helen\n|[[American Airlines Theatre]], Broadway\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Indian Ink]]''\n|Eleanor Swan\n|[[Roundabout Theatre Company|Laura Pels Theatre]], Off-Broadway\n|-\n|2018-19\n|''[[My Fair Lady (musical)|My Fair Lady]]''\n|Mrs. Higgins\n|[[Vivian Beaumont Theatre]], Broadway\n|}\n\n=== Video games ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|1998\n|''[[Dark Side of the Moon: A Sci-Fi Adventure|Dark Side of the Moon]]''\n|Miner Woman (voice role)\n|[[PC game|PC]] version for [[Windows 9x|Windows 95/98]]\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n=== Film accolades ===\n'''Academy Award'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Category\n!Results\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Tom & Viv (film)|Tom & Viv]]''\n|[[Academy Award for Best Actress in a Supporting Role|Best Actress in a Supporting Role]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n'''BAFTA Awards'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Category\n!Results\n|-\n|1984\n|''[[The Ploughman's Lunch]]''\n|[[BAFTA Award for Best Actress in a Supporting Role|Best Actress in a Supporting Role]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Gotham Awards'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Category\n!Results\n|-\n|2007\n|''[[Before the Devil Knows You're Dead]]''\n|[[Gotham Independent Film Award for Best Ensemble Cast|Best Ensemble Cast]]\n|{{WON}}\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Critics Choice Film Awards'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Category\n!Results\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Before the Devil Knows You're Dead|Before the Devil Know's You're Dead]]''\n|[[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Acting Ensemble|Best Acting Ensemble]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|}\n\n'''National Board of Review'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Category\n!Results\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Tom & Viv]]''\n|[[National Board of Review Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n|{{WON}}\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Television accolades ===\n'''Primetime Emmy Award'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Category\n!Results\n|-\n|1976\n|''[[Notorious Woman]]''\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Limited Series or Movie|Best Lead Actress in a Limited Series]]\n|{{win}}\n|-\n|1978\n|''[[Holocaust (miniseries)|Holocaust]]''\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Limited Series or Movie|Best Lead Actress in a Limited Series]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Golden Globe Awards'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Category\n!Results\n|-\n| 1976\n|''[[Notorious Woman]]''\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Television Series Drama|Best Actress in a Television Series \u2013 Drama]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|1978\n|''[[Holocaust (miniseries)|Holocaust]]''\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Television Series Drama|Best Actress in a Television Series - Drama]]\n|{{win}}\n|}\n\n=== Theatre accolades ===\n'''Tony Awards'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Category\n!Results\n|-\n|1966\n|''[[The Lion in Winter]]''\n|[[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Play|Best Actress in a Play]]\n|{{WON}}<ref name=\"TonyAwards\">{{cite news |title=Search Past Tony Award Winners and Nominees |url=https://www.tonyawards.com/en_US/history/pastwinners/tonys_results.html?lname=rosemary+harris |accessdate=4 August 2018 |publisher=[[Tony Awards]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|1972\n|''[[Old Times]]''\n| [[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Play|Best Actress in a Play]]\n|{{Nominated}}<ref name=\"TonyAwards\"/>\n|-\n|1976 \n|''[[The Royal Family (play)|The Royal Family]]''  \n|[[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Play|Best Actress in a Play]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|1984\n|''[[Heartbreak House]]''\n|[[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Play|Best Actress in a Play]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1985\n|''[[Pack of Lies]]''\n|[[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Play|Best Actress in a Play]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1986 \n|''[[Hay Fever (play)|Hay Fever]]''\n|[[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Play|Best Actress in a Play]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1996\n|''[[A Delicate Balance (play)|A Delicate Balance]]''\n|[[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Play|Best Actress in a Play]] \n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[Waiting in the Wings (play)|Waiting in the Wings]]''\n|[[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Play|Best Actress in a Play]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[The Royal Family (play)|The Royal Family]]''\n|[[Tony Award for Best Featured Actress in a Play|Best Featured Actress in a Play]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2019\n| \n|[[Special Tony Award|Lifetime Achievement in the Theatre]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Drama Desk Award''' \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Category\n!Results\n|-\n|1972\n|''[[Old Times]]''\n|Best Performance\n|{{win}}<ref name=\"ibdb.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibdb.com/broadway-cast-staff/rosemary-harris-44269/#awards|title=Rosemary Harris \u2013 Broadway Cast & Staff &#124; IBDB|website=www.ibdb.com|accessdate=5 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|1973\n|''[[A Streetcar Named Desire (play)|A Streetcar Named Desire]]''\n|Best Performance\n|{{win}}<ref name=\"ibdb.com\"/>\n|-\n|1973\n|''[[The Merchant of Venice]]'' \n|Best Performance\n|{{win}}<ref name=\"ibdb.com\"/>\n|-\n|1976\n|''[[The Royal Family (play)|The Royal Family]]''\n|[[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Actress in a Play|Actress in a Play]]\n|{{win}}\n|-\n|1984\n|''[[Heartbreak House]]''\n|[[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Actress in a Play|Actress in a Play]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1985\n|''[[Pack of Lies (play)|Pack of Lies]]''\n|[[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Actress in a Play|Actress in a Play]]\n|{{win}}\n|-\n|1996 \n|''[[A Delicate Balance (play)|A Delicate Balance]]''\n|[[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Actress in a Play|Actress in a Play]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Laurence Olivier Award'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Category\n!Results\n|-\n|1981\n|''[[All My Sons]]''\n|[[Laurence Olivier Award for Actress of the Year in a Revival|Actress in a Revival]] \n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1983\n|''[[Heartbreak House]]''\n|[[Laurence Olivier Award for Actress of the Year in a Revival|Ac